Char Siu Chicken

1/3  ketchup
1/4 c brown sugar
1/4 c honey
1/4 c shoyu
2 tbsp sriracha
2 tbsp shaoxing rice wine
1 tbsp hoisin sauce
1 tsp 5 spice powder
1 tsp sesame oil
1 small (6oz) red beet, peeled and roughly chopped
3 1/2-4lb chicken, cut into 8 pieces
2 tbsp vegetable oil
kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

In a blender, combine the ketchup, sugar, honey, shoyu, sriracha, wine, hoisin sauce, 5 spice powder, sesame oil, and chopped beet. Puree until smooth. Transfer to a sealable plastic bag, add the chicken and shake to coat. Marinate in the refrigerator overnight. The next day, prep a grill. Remove the chicken from the marinade, wiping off any excess and place in a medium bowl. Toss with the vegetable oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill, turning as needed, until charred and reading 165F on a meat thermometer. Transfer to a platter and let rest for 5 min before serving.
